	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ah, dammit! I just ordered some of the NJM2267, but I had to order surface mounted because I could only find DIP on eBay from China. I just checked, Mouser has the NJM2268 DIP in stock.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /> <br /><br />Well at any rate, I too ordered a couple NJM amps, as well as a few THS7314 amps and a slew of caps. I just wish I would have known that the NJM's had a newer version, I had to buy some SOIC-DIP adapters so I can breadboard with them. The only thing, those NJM's aren't exactly SOIC. They're a package that the manufacture calls &quot;DMP.&quot; A little Googling told me that they have the same leg spacing as SOIC, but the package is a little wider. So they probably wont fit on regular SOIC adapter boards. I paid a premium for some <a href="http://www.schmartboard.com/" class="postlink">Schmart Boards</a> because their &quot;EZ&quot; adapter boards have much longer pads to make soldering surface mounted stuff a little easier. I'm hoping the longer pads will allow me to use this DMP package. If not, I'll have to hand wire them to pin headers so I can breadboard with them. <br /><br /><br />Long story short, the only two things I'm not 100% on is:<br /><br />1): AC or DC coupled output ? <br /><br />2): Best way to kill the voltage on the Pr and Pb lines without effecting the image quality?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


